						<summary>

						<p>Partly illegible. Refers to a gift of land made presumably to a temple for the merit of <hi rend="bold">Guṇḍaya-Nāyuḍu</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Māraya-Sāhiṇi</hi> while <hi rend="bold">Māchaya-Sāhiṇi</hi> was governing the <hi rend="bold">Gurindāla, Piṅgali</hi> and other provinces as dependent of <hi rend="bold">Pratāpa-Rudradēva.</hi></p>						

						<p>Perhaps this <hi rend="bold">Māraya-Sāhiṇi</hi> is identical with the person of that name to whom a portion of <hi rend="italic">Bhāskara-Rāmāyaṇam</hi> is dedicated.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
